radreport-templates — Licensing

This repository is dual-licensed. The applicable license depends on the type
of the asset:

1. Software components — all files under shared/scripts/, together with any
   other build or utility scripts (e.g. *.js) — are licensed under the
   MIT License. See LICENSE-MIT.

2. Template and documentation content — all report templates (*.html and
   *.source.html), stylesheets (*.css), frontmatter (*.yaml), RadLex/LOINC
   mapping tables and all documentation (*.md) — are licensed under the
   Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0).
   See LICENSE-CC-BY-4.0.

Where a single file combines both (e.g. an HTML template containing inline
JavaScript), the CC BY 4.0 terms govern the file as a whole, with the MIT
grant additionally applying to the embedded software portions.

Templates derived from the DRG AK Befundung project (CT Urolithiasis,
CT Lungenarterien) incorporate material originally licensed under CC BY 4.0
by the Deutsche Röntgengesellschaft; attribution is retained in the respective
template README files. Source: https://github.com/DRGagit/ak_befundung

